io.dazraf.vertx.futures.http

Class HttpClientRequestWithFutureResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.dazraf.vertx.futures.http.HttpClientRequestWithFutureResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    io.vertx.core.AsyncResult<io.vertx.core.http.HttpClientResponse>, io.vertx.core.Future<io.vertx.core.http.HttpClientResponse>

    public class HttpClientRequestWithFutureResponse
extends Object
implements io.vertx.core.Future<io.vertx.core.http.HttpClientResponse>
    Instances of this class:
    1. wrap an existing HttpClientRequest
    2. present all methods specified by HttpClientRequest
    3. implement Future<HttpClientResponse>

    This means that one can use this class to chain http operations.

    e.g. 
     
 when(future(httpClient.get("/")).end())
 .onSuccess(HttpFutures::checkHttpSuccess)
 .then(response -> bodyObject(response))
 .onSuccess(body -> assertThat(context, body.containsKey("time"), is(true)))
 .onFail((Runnable) context::fail);
